4.4. Model Development 
Data Generators 
Data generators play an important role in the implementation process by feeding the data into 
the neural network in batches and splitting the dataset into training, validation, and test sets. 
The create_data_generators function is designed to smoothen this process. It starts by 
applying rescaling to normalise the pixel values of the images. For the training data, it utilises 
a validation split of 0.3, meaning that 30% of the training data is reserved for validation 
purposes. This is accomplished through the ImageDataGenerator class from the Keras library, 
which handles the data augmentation and preparation tasks. The function creates distinct data 
generators for training, validation, and testing datasets. The training and validation generators 
are derived from the same training folder, with the validation subset specified, while the test 
generator is derived from a distinct test folder. These generators load images in grayscale 
mode, ensuring consistency in the input data format for the neural network, and process the 
images in batches, thus optimising memory usage and computational efficiency during model 
training and evaluation. 
