4.6. Model Evaluation 
In the model evaluation step, the performance of the developed Convolutional Neural Network 
(CNN) and Visual Geometry Group (VGG16) models is exactly assessed on the chosen test 
dataset. This evaluation aims to measure the effectiveness of the models in accurately detecting 
and classifying defects within Betaguard sealing cases. By using a set of metrics including 
accuracy, precision, recall, and F1-score, the models' predictive capabilities are systematically 
examined. Accuracy serves as a fundamental measure of overall correctness, while precision 
quantifies the proportion of true positive predictions among all positive predictions. Similarly, 
recall measures the proportion of true positive predictions among all actual positives. The F1
score, being the harmonic mean of precision and recall, provides a balanced assessment of the 
models' performance, considering both false positives and false negatives. Through proper 
evaluation, valuable insights are achieved into the models' capabilities, enabling informed 
decision-making and guiding potential enhancements in the defect detection system. 
Performance Metrics 
Performance metrics serve as quantitative measures of model performance, supporting 
comparison and assessment across different models and evaluation criteria. The following 
metrics are computed during the validation process: 
Accuracy: The proportion of correctly classified sealing cases out of the total number of 
instances. 
Precision: The ratio of true positive predictions to the total number of positive predictions, 
indicating the model's ability to avoid false positives. 
Recall: The ratio of true positive predictions to the total number of actual positive instances, 
reflecting the model's ability to capture all positive instances. 
F1-Score: The harmonic mean of precision and recall, providing a balanced measure of the 
model's performance across precision and recall. 
Classification Report (Precision, Recall, and F1-Score) 
Classification report metrics provide precision, recall, f1-score, and support for each class. 
Precision = TP / (TP+FP). 
Recall = TP / (TP+FN). 
F1-Score = 2 (Precision recall) / (Precision + recall) 
Support - It represents number of occurrences of particular class is in True. 
