Overview 
The baseline Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) model was trained in four categories: No 
Defects, Crack, Uneven Seal, and Seal Overflow. The model's performance was evaluated using 
standard metrics like recall, accuracy, precision, and F1-score. A summary of the evaluation's 
findings is provided below. 
Test Accuracy and Loss 
Test Accuracy: On the test dataset, the model achieved an accuracy of 88.75%, meaning that 
about 89 of the 100 predictions the model produced were accurate. 
• Test Loss: The test loss, which calculates the prediction error of the model, is 0.2187. In this 
case, a loss of 0.2187 shows that the model is performing better than average, with a lower loss 
indicating improved model performance. 
Classification Report 
Complete performance metrics, including as precision, recall, and F1-score for every class, are 
provided in the classification report. 
