Model Architecture and Training 
The three layers that comprise up the CNN model architecture remain convolutional, max
pooling, and fully connected. All images undergo the same preparation methods prior to being 
fed into the model. The network is trained using the sparse categorical cross-entropy loss 
function, the Adam optimizer, early stopping, and model checkpointing to avoid overfitting. A 
range of performance criteria, including F1-score, recall, accuracy, and precision, were used to 
evaluate convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for defect identification. These measurements 
offer a thorough understanding of how well the model detects defects. 
