crack on a defect-free image. Although the confidence level was lower (0.52), the 
misclassification indicates a potential issue with oversensitivity to certain visual features, 
leading to false positives. The model performed well in detecting seal overflow and uneven seal 
defects, with high confidence and precise bounding boxes, showcasing its strong capability in 
these categories. Despite these successes, the misclassification in the "No Defects" category 
suggests that further refinement is necessary, particularly in improving the model's robustness 
in distinguishing defect-free images from those with subtle defects. This will enhance overall 
model reliability in real-world applications.  
