resources by identifying problems before they lead to faulty products. This supports the 
automotive industry's move towards more sustainable practices, particularly important 
in the production of electric vehicles. 
 Economic Implications: For Volvo Cars, improving defect detection can lower 
production costs, reduce recalls, and decrease the need for rework, leading to better 
overall efficiency. These benefits contribute to higher productivity and profitability, 
helping the company stay competitive. The savings can also be reinvested in further 
innovation, driving growth. 
 Technological Advancement: This project represents progress in using machine 
learning and computer vision in manufacturing. Successfully applying these 
technologies enhances Volvo Cars’ production capabilities and contributes to 
advancing industrial automation standards. 
 Accessibility and Affordability: Although the initiative is centred toward large
scale manufacturing, it also takes into account the wider implications of providing these 
technology to smaller producers. More firms can gain from higher quality and 
efficiency when the system is scalable and affordable. 
By considering these ethical and societal factors, the research not only achieves its technical 
goals but also contributes positively to society while maintaining ethical integrity. 
