7. Conclusion 
This research has demonstrated the practicality of using Convolutional Neural Networks 
(CNNs), particularly the VGG16 model, for the automated detection of defects in Betaguard 
yellow seals. Through the effective use of transfer learning, data augmentation, and 
regularization techniques, the model achieved an impressive 93% accuracy rate. This level of 
performance indicates that CNNs hold significant promise in enhancing quality control 
processes within the manufacturing sector, providing a scalable and efficient tool for 
identifying defects. The acceptance of such technology could lead to notable developments in 
both product safety and manufacturing efficiency. 
The study discovered certain drawbacks, particularly the model's inability to discriminate 
between defects that have similar visible characteristics. This implies that more investigation 
and improvement are possible to increase the adaptability of the model. 
7.1 Future Work 
Moving forward, several avenues for further research are evident. One key area involves 
expanding the dataset to include a broader range of images with higher resolution. Such 
enhancements could address the model’s current challenges in identifying subtle and visually 
similar defects. Collaborations with industry partners to gather more diverse and extensive 
datasets would be particularly advantageous. 
Furthermore, exploring more current and advanced CNN architectures such ResNet or 
EfficientNet, may result in additional advancements in generalization and accuracy. To find if 
Vision Transformer models may provide even more improvements in defect identification, it 
might also be worthwhile to look into the possible advantages of employing them. These 
models have shown success in other areas of computer vision. 
Incorporating explainable AI methods is yet another exciting approach. By simplifying the 
model's decision-making process, these approaches will promote satisfying regulatory 
requirements and increase operational transparency. 
Eventually, in order to ensure that these aspects are carefully regulated when this technology 
is more extensively used, it will be essential to take into account the ethical implications, such 
as the possible influence on jobs and data privacy concerns. 
